==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hounds-tongue
<hw>Hound's"-tongue`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hundes tunge</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A biennial weed
(<spn>Cynoglossum officinale</spn>), with soft tongue-shaped leaves, and
an offensive odor. It bears nutlets covered with barbed or hooked
prickles. Called also <altname>dog's-tongue</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Houp</ent>⟦br⟧
